{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"287422c4-360e-41ab-afcb-3201c693937c","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws<T>` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName);\n}\n```\n\n**Why modernize?**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs (e.g., the constructor could throw instead of `CreateUser`).\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call and lets you inspect the exception (message, properties, inner exception).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f0884cb7-f54e-4efc-a569-a1bd236676e6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question - no tools needed.","outputTokens":247,"requestId":"9820:24F978:10D7064:150E5BB:69FFDFCC"},"id":"55b95c8f-6cf6-4a0b-8e9a-22e704200cac","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:30:58.728Z","parentId":"d5602598-bb5b-4c77-ae89-d9b6ef7e827a"}
